<h4><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-7822" src="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/teachers/audrey-bennett_150.jpg" alt="audrey-bennett_150" width="150" height="149" />Audrey Bennett, CT</h4>
<strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:audbenn@hotmail.com" target="_blank">audbenn@hotmail.com</a>
Audrey began self-study into Indigenous Wisdom and Earth based medicine paths in 1996. She began apprenticeship with don Oscar in 2008. Her hearts work and dedication to "all our relations" also took her through formal commitments in First Nations traditions of the Plains People, as well as working with Alberto Villoldo, Linda Fitch and don Martin Pineado from Wasau, Peru. Her formal education in Social Work and pursuit of the Pachakuti Mesa Tradition unite in bringing practical and meaningful depth to her teaching. Yet "Great Mystery" guides the "hollow bone". Audrey is a forensic social worker and has a private Integrative Psychotherapy practice as well. She is the founder of Weave Your Life LLC &amp; The Center for Holistic Practices &amp; Psychotherapy in Southington, CT.
